zlog

C In-memory Logging Library

Hompage: http://fclose.com/p/zlog/

*Introduction*

zlog is a C in-memory logging library. It allocates a buffer in memory for logging, and flush the buffer to the log file (or stdout) when the buffer is full, or flushed explicitly by the program or flushing thread. 

*Source code*

Source code of mrcc can be downloaded from http://github.com/zma/zlog/ .

*Author*

Zhiqiang Ma. http://fclose.com/zma/
